          <p>In theory, the model works like this: rent a one-bedroom condo for $2,200 per month, earn $4,000 in Airbnb revenue, and keep $1,800 after expenses. In practice, particularly in a heavily regulated and high-rent market like Toronto, the numbers rarely line up that cleanly.</p>

